parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure and Abnormal Oil Consumption
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. Abnormal oil consumption can lead to engine damage and premature wear.
symptoms: knocking noise when driven longer than 10 minutes
sudden drop in oil level without warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty timing chains can cause engine misfiring, stalling, and unreliable engine performance, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: engine stalling or cutting out while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to shut down or stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle shutting down and not restarting
check engine warning light illuminating intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine performance issues can cause hesitation, surging, and pinging/knocking, which can lead to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: especially in second gear at steady throttle around 2k rpm.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system issues can cause antifreeze leaks, which can lead to engine damage and overheating.
symptoms: Smell of antifreeze inside the driver's compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to brake unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control, and can also lead to increased stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the brake pedal is harder to push
the vehicle takes longer to stop
a high-pitched noise is heard while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent starting issues can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leaving the driver stranded, and can also lead to increased wear on the starter and battery.
symptoms: but the engine does not start
the brake pedal is harder to push when the issue occurs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission and engine performance issues can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control, and can also lead to increased wear on the transmission and engine.
symptoms: The engine and transmission continue to push the vehicle when braking
the vehicle takes longer to slow down
the vehicle slows down faster when put in neutral.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected explosion of the sunroof or panoramic roof can cause injuries from shattered glass, driver distraction, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Sunroof or panoramic roof shatters or explodes without warning
causing glass to fall into the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Control Module (ECM) Failure and Related Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or shudder, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: engine light comes on and goes off
and the vehicle lags when turning on and off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning backup camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries while reversing, especially in low-visibility conditions.
symptoms: The backup camera screen glitches or goes black
making it difficult or impossible to see behind the vehicle while reversing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without pressing the gas pedal
often at low speeds (less than 25 mph)
and may continue to accelerate even when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission slips at various intervals
often accompanied by hesitation or loss of power
and may not be accompanied by any warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transfer Case and Axle Seal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case and axle seal can cause fluid leaks, leading to premature wear on the transmission and drivetrain components, and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transfer case and axle seal start leaking
